law.catch_line: Violation of duties for which no other penalty provided.
law.text: Any public officer who willfully neglects to perform a duty imposed upon him under the election laws, for which no other penalty is provided, or who willfully performs such duty in a way that hinders the objects of the election laws, shall be guilty of a Class B misdemeanor.
law.history: Amended 1990 Ky. Acts ch. 48, sec. 81, effective July 13, 1990. -- Created 1974 Ky. Acts ch. 130, sec. 87.
